node.text: “The life and spirituality that you build is always going to be better than one given to you” Amen sister.
#religion #nononsensespirituality
“The life and spirituality that you build is always going to be better than one given to you” Amen sister.
@njneb_ Following
@annoflineandcircle sorry what do you mean by following?
What about Gnosticism

@jillyblades there are many religions that tell you to take care of the poor or have a system of ethics. But Judaism did something no other religion did. Because it valued conversation so much it was able to adapt and change as it went, and even secularize. It’s not uncommon in America to have atheist rabbis, because many of the truth claims along the way have been dropped but they’ve been able to hold onto their culture and rituals anyways. Not all religions can do that, but Judaism can because they valued the continuing conversation over old truth claims.
@jillyblades exactly this was so weird , makes no sense long form conversations?😮
@esta_on_insta we have very few conversations that are 5,000 years long. They have one of the few.

I love your content but am wondering: Judaism is an ancient religion full of scholarship on morality and ethics and the original theology commanding us to care for the sick and poor. “Long-form conversation” is your favorite thing you’ve gotten from the religious aspect of Judaism? Can you tell me more about what that means?
@abstractroses101 it’s a political religion at this point

@nononsensespirituality Came here to ask you your thoughts on UU! Do you mean it functions as a political action group? If so, how is that different from the Black churches that actively and materially supported the Civil Rights movement?
Try Unitarian Universalism
Leave your truth claims and bs behind: yes.👏
"Scientology: eeeeugh what not to do." 😂😂😂❤️
Give it all to me 👏👏👏🙌🙌
Your content has been exactly what I’m needing. Thank you.
So good! ❤️
@boy_named_kelly same
Diito
@boy_named_kelly as Richard Rohr says no one does first half of life better than Mormons, and no one does second half of life worse than Mormons. It’s incredibly damaging for adult human development.
I’m a member of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints and I consider myself a Christian as well
What an extraordinary well based brief explanation of the qualities of each main religion.
